                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17192636" author="altanozlu" created="Wed, 9 Sep 2020 05:32:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My bad, server is using JVM 11 and nodetool client using JVM 8 that is the reason.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17230317" author="dcapwell" created="Thu, 12 Nov 2020 01:20:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have seen this as well with server running JVM 11 and nodetool JVM 11, the issue went away on restart.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I took a dump of the metrics and saw that the tables had the MBeans registered, but not TableMetrics (though some tables had both).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am trying to figure out how this happened and will reopen if I make any progress.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17236443" author="dcapwell" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2020 21:15:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Confirmed this is actually an issue, and is unrelated to JDK version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17236448" author="dcapwell" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2020 21:23:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems global static state was added to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7273&quot; title=&quot;expose global ColumnFamily metrics&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7273&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7273&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with names that are lower case, so all the cleanup logic for a single table attempts to delete all global metrics...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17236460" author="dcapwell" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2020 21:40:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tested on 3.0 and not able to replicate, so looks like &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7273&quot; title=&quot;expose global ColumnFamily metrics&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7273&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7273&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; didn&apos;t do this but something over time saw the lower case global static field and tried to use it differently.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17236526" author="dcapwell" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2020 23:51:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jon +1ed in GH&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17236537" author="jmeredithco" created="Sat, 21 Nov 2020 00:19:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 from me&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17236543" author="yifanc" created="Sat, 21 Nov 2020 00:27:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue is caused static value &lt;tt&gt;TableMetrics#all&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;br/&gt;
The patch looks good overall. Left several small comments in the PR. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17236565" author="yifanc" created="Sat, 21 Nov 2020 02:21:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the fix. +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17242679" author="jrwest" created="Wed, 2 Dec 2020 20:02:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 LGTM&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
